Nigeria Plans to Boost Lending for Agriculture, ThisDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-06-28T08:25:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-28/nigeria-plans-to-boost-lending-for-agriculture-thisday-says.html
Nigeria ’s central bank plans to
mobilize about 450 billion naira ($2.9 billion) from commercial
banks for lending to the agriculture industry,  ThisDay  reported,
citing Paul Eluhaiwe, a director of the bank’s Development
Finance Department.  The central bank aims to raise agriculture lending to 10
percent of total loans in the banking industry in five years,
from the current 2 percent, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 